1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,033
<i>I'll believe in politicians
more than you!</i>

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:14,567
<i>- Liar!
- There, oh, look!</i>

3
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:15,833
<i> You've become undercover,</i>

4
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:17,400
<i>o you'll be part
of the first family.</i>

5
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>- You're lucky.
- Yes, you are.</i>

6
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>When you cut off
one head of the snake,</i>

7
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:21,833
<i> a new one will sprout.</i>

8
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:22,967
<i> That's why I want you to know</i>

9
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:25,033
<i>who the new enemy
of Calabari is.</i>

10
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:26,567
<i>I really feel like
this is a hate crime.</i>

11
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,767
<i>Imagine, this is already
the second death</i>

12
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> in a row in our sisterhood.</i>

13
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,033
<i> Don't worry, Tootsie.</i>

14
00:00:32,167 --> 00:00:33,667
<i>We'll hunt down the one
who killed you,</i>

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,433
<i>even if it means it will
put us in danger.</i>

16
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:40,067
<i>I just want to know
if you told Chief that I did it</i>

17
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>because I wanted to help
the case.</i>

18
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>Bobby, I'm just protecting you
from yourself.</i>

19
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:47,300
<i>Sometimes, we don't need sermons
and worries.</i>

20
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:49,467
<i> Sometimes, we just an ally.</i>

21
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,667
<i> Did you two fight?</i>

22
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,733
<i>It's your first day here,
Lieutenant Samson</i>

23
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:53,967
<i>and you're gossiping right away?</i>

24
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:56,033
<i>My only advice to you is,
if you really like Tonyo,</i>

25
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:57,633
<i> don't be too fussy, okay?</i>

26
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:00,300
<i>Maybe Tonyo will find someone
better than you,</i>

27
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,133
<i> especially since I'm here.</i>

28
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:05,700
<i>No matter how you look at it,
it's not your fault.</i>

29
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:08,633
<i>So help us so that
there aren't more victims.</i>

30
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,933
<i> Your hunch is right, Tonyo.</i>

31
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,533
<i>I saw something
in my vision</i>

32
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:14,433
<i>that there will be
another victim.</i>

33
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,467
Where is Bautista?

34
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,900
She's so tiny that is why
she's hard to find.

35
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:25,200
Oh, Bok, it seems like
you're looking for someone.

36
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:27,300
So what's Chief's new assignment
for you?

37
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:29,900
Oh...

38
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:30,867
Nothing!

39
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,600
You know that,
same old-same old,

40
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:35,833
like this, like that.

41
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:38,333
I'm serious.

42
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:39,700
You know, I'm really fed up

43
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,633
with the fugitive
we're looking for.

44
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,233
Why don't you let me in on that?

45
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,800
Do you really want to know?

46
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:51,967
This is just between us.

47
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:55,300
Because Chief knows I'm so good,

48
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:58,533
he gave me a special mission.

49
00:01:58,667 --> 00:01:59,533
That sounds okay.

50
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:01,200
Include me in that...

51
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:02,867
so I have something to do.

52
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,900
Don't you understand?

53
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:09,100
Special mission,
special assignment.

54
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:13,067
That's for special officers
like me.

55
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:16,267
If you compare it with dessert,
you're just a regular.

56
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:20,267
Me, with leche flan,
special.

57
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,533
Okay?

58
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,433
Oh, Bautista, I've been
contacting you for a while now.

59
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:28,000
Why?

60
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:30,233
You will be blessed today.

61
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:32,433
Come with me,
we're going somewhere.

62
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:33,867
Where are we going, Sir?

63
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:34,967
Don't ask too many questions.

64
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:36,200
Just come with me.

65
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,633
Let's go.

66
00:02:48,467 --> 00:02:50,900
Ma'am Bobby,
you're so busy.

67
00:02:54,767 --> 00:02:56,800
These are old murder cases.

68
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:58,433
What are you looking for?

69
00:02:58,567 --> 00:03:02,433
Well, I thought, since
I'm just here at the precinct,

70
00:03:02,567 --> 00:03:03,633
I have nothing else to do

71
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:06,167
to help find the gay killer.

72
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,633
So I'm reviewing
these old cases.

73
00:03:08,767 --> 00:03:10,033
Maybe there's something similar

74
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:11,367
to the gay killer's modus
operandi.

75
00:03:11,767 --> 00:03:13,433
This is quite a lot, huh?

76
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:14,333
Yes.

77
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,067
What? Do you want to help?

78
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,867
- Sure, Ma'am.
- Come on.

79
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:53,167
Lieutenant, good morning.

80
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,167
Sir, thank you very much

81
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:58,067
for accommodating us
even on short notice.

82
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,933
You know, I really want to close

83
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:03,867
all the holes in Mando's escape.

84
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,433
My name is being tarnished.

85
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:07,067
Don't worry.

86
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:11,367
Our mission is to find out
who let Mando escape.

87
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:12,833
Lieutenant, let's sit down.

88
00:04:14,533 --> 00:04:17,233
We've done our own
investigation here,

89
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:23,000
and one of our jail guards
is involved.

90
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:26,367
He's the one who gave Mando
the extra key.

91
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,600
Didn't they say why he did that?

92
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,267
Did someone order him?

93
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,533
Mando gave him 100,000 pesos.

94
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,467
100,000 pesos?

95
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,133
How did Mando
get that much money?

96
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,867
That's what remains
a mystery to us.

97
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,667
There are CCTVs
in the visiting area.

98
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,000
And we've reviewed all
the footage of Mando

99
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,833
and his visitors.

100
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,767
We didn't see anyone

101
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:51,367
handing over money or anything.

102
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,900
Unless...

103
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:54,833
the payment happened outside.

104
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:58,633
Can we take a look
at your CCTV footage?

105
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:01,267
Okay, I'll send it here.

106
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:38,633
Oh, Mister, good afternoon.

107
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:39,967
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

108
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:42,500
Oh, I'm Mira,
I'm a journalist.

109
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,233
Just a question.

110
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:47,300
This is Sitio Manggahan, right?

111
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:48,300
This is it, Ma'am.

112
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:49,400
Because three years ago,

113
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:53,167
there was a big road development
project here.

114
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:56,233
Where is the said road?

115
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:00,200
Oh, why?

116
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:03,500
This is it, right here,
where we are standing.

117
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:05,333
Sir?

118
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:07,433
What happened?
Didn't it push through?

119
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,233
This is it.

120
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:12,533
We thought our lives
would be better here.

121
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,000
It's just a drawing.

122
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:16,400
We have a hard time
when it rains.

123
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:17,400
It's so muddy!

124
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:18,800
Is it correct that
this is the project

125
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:22,033
of the Former Councilor
Glen Guerrero?

126
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:23,667
Yes.

127
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:47,700
Mom.

128
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,267
You can't be serious.

129
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,200
Give me that.
That's enough, please.

130
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:54,367
I'll just finish this.

131
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,533
No, Mom.
You're done, okay?

132
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,667
Mom, I'm being proclaimed

133
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,100
as the new mayor
of Calabari today.

134
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:02,433
I need you.

135
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:05,067
I need you in this moment.

136
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,633
Oh, sorry, Glen.

137
00:07:07,767 --> 00:07:11,733
You know, everything
is happening all at once.

138
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:14,700
First, your dad's death,

139
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,633
and then his last will.

140
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:19,167
Yes, I understand, Mom.

141
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,667
There are a lot of things

142
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,633
our family is going through
this year.

143
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:25,167
But let's use this moment

144
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:28,933
for change for our family.

145
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:31,233
I like the sound of that.

146
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:36,700
Wait. Where is your sister?

147
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:40,100
Oh, I don't know.

148
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:42,500
She should be coming,
she said she has a plus one,

149
00:07:42,767 --> 00:07:45,367
so maybe she'll just come
any time.

150
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:47,000
Plus one?

151
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:50,633
How about Cecilia?
Is she coming?

152
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:53,733
She said she's busy.

153
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:55,100
Excuse me, Mayor.

154
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:57,067
We're about to start.

155
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,467
Okay.

156
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:03,500
I still can't believe

157
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:06,833
they killed Zondra
and Tootsie.

158
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:08,233
That's right.

159
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:10,933
They're both kind.

160
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:12,533
You're right.

161
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:17,300
My wife is so kind.

162
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,500
My wife...

163
00:08:25,533 --> 00:08:26,900
Tootsie!

164
00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:34,467
Tootsie, my love!

165
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:36,533
Tootsie!

166
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:40,167
Excuse me.

167
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,067
Who are you?

168
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,033
Tootsie's wife.

169
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,267
- Wife?
- Tootsie.

170
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,400
Are you sure?

171
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:53,633
Tootsie is gay.

172
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:55,800
I know!

173
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:58,433
I'm Tootsie's wife, right?

174
00:08:59,567 --> 00:09:01,267
Who are you?

175
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,367
I'm her partner!

176
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,167
Partner?

177
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,400
Tootsie and I are married
in the Church.

178
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:12,967
That's impossible!

179
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:17,233
As far as I know,
Tootsie is single!

180
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:18,900
So please,

181
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:21,467
if you want to cause trouble,
not here!

182
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,000
Let's respect the dead!

183
00:09:23,133 --> 00:09:25,300
Are you throwing me out?

184
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,800
You're the one
who should leave

185
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:32,167
because I have a right
to my husband!

186
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,433
You're just a mistress!

187
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,233
Excuse me!

188
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:41,300
I won't let you disrespect me
in front of Tootsie!

189
00:09:41,433 --> 00:09:42,500
Fool!

190
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:48,100
Tootsie is my husband!

191
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,533
Look at this, Noble.

192
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:55,167
I saw another one.

193
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:59,133
Both cold cases
of this murder in 2018.

194
00:09:59,267 --> 00:10:01,833
They have the same modus
operandi as our killer today.

195
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,367
This, too, Ma'am.

196
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,933
An icepick was also used,
and the victim is also gay.

197
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:11,333
And all of these unsolved cases.

198
00:10:11,467 --> 00:10:13,067
The killer has not been
caught yet.

199
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,967
What do you think, Ma'am?

200
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:17,967
I think...

201
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,367
it's possible that
the person who did this,

202
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:24,467
and our killer today
are the same.

203
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:27,533
You mean a serial killer?

204
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:31,767
Hey, what's with you?

205
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,433
That's enough!
That's enough!

206
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:35,567
- Don't fight here!
- Wait!

207
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:38,733
Can you respect Tootsie?

208
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,400
You both loved her, right?

209
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:42,800
Do you think Tootsie
will be happy

210
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,200
with what you're doing?

211
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:47,367
Tootsie!

212
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:52,333
Sorry!

213
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:55,067
- What a shame...
- Sorry.

214
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,333
What a shame...

215
00:10:56,467 --> 00:10:58,100
Sorry.

216
00:10:58,233 --> 00:11:01,067
I didn't even catch her alive.

217
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,767
She said she'll come back to us,

218
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,200
that she will come home
last weekend.

219
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:07,367
Tootsie...

220
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,700
Sorry...

221
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:11,133
I'm sorry too.

222
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,667
I miss Tootsie so much, too.

223
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,400
I miss her.

224
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:21,600
Tootsie...

225
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,967
Sorry!

226
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:36,833
I'm sorry!

227
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:44,733
We really need to do
something, Abdul.

228
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:47,667
We can't just sit around,

229
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:52,000
waiting for Bobby
and their investigation.

230
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:54,867
Even if we're at risk becoming
a killer's target

231
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,133
because of our beauty?

232
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:58,133
Yes.

233
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:00,433
Because if he really kills
homosexuals

234
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:02,233
because of a hate crime...

235
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:05,333
we are all in danger.

236
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,800
- I...
- I...

237
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:13,800
State your name.

238
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:14,967
Glen Guerrero.

239
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:16,533
Of the City of Calabari...

240
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:18,200
Of the City of Calabari...

241
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:20,167
Having by operation of law...

242
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:22,167
Having by operation of law...

243
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:25,100
Succeed into the position
of mayor of Calabari City...

244
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:27,967
Succeed into the position
of mayor of Calabari City...

245
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,400
Do hereby...

246
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:30,367
Do hereby...

247
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,567
Solemnly swear...

248
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:32,600
Solemnly swear...

249
00:12:32,733 --> 00:12:35,033
That I will faithfully
discharge...

250
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,300
Upon reviewing,

251
00:12:44,433 --> 00:12:47,700
there are very few people
who have visited Mando

252
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,267
for the past 6 months.

253
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,900
And...

254
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:53,667
journalist, social worker

255
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,433
they're frequent here.

256
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:56,600
But...

257
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:59,100
there's one person we didn't do
a background check on.

258
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:00,367
Can we see it?

259
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:04,733
Him.

260
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:07,500
I don't know if he put
a fake name in the logbook.

261
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:09,533
Can we ask for a copy of this?

262
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:12,300
Yes, okay.
I'll send you a copy.

263
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,767
Why, Sir? Do you know him?

264
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:18,733
He looks familiar.

265
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,900
Sir, come in, the boss has been
waiting for a while.

266
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,600
Okay.

267
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:33,433
How many more are we going
to go through, Roman?

268
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:35,367
Oh, there's a lot more.

269
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,333
If you want,
let's split the work.

270
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,733
You go at the gambling den,
and I'll go at the girly bar.

271
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,367
Hey!

272
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:46,400
No, why don't we do this,
let's reverse it.

273
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:48,433
I'll go to the gambling den,
and you'll go at the girly bar.

274
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,400
That's it, that's it,
I like that.

275
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:52,300
Let's start with this.

276
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:01,200
It's good that you're here.

277
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,100
I've been waiting for you
for a while.

278
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,167
Oh.

279
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,200
Is this complete?

280
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:06,733
Of course!

281
00:14:07,967 --> 00:14:08,900
Wow...

282
00:14:09,033 --> 00:14:10,567
your gambling den
is getting successful.

283
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,233
Yes, because my customers
are increasing.

284
00:14:13,367 --> 00:14:16,400
So next time,
there will be more.

285
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,367
This will make the Boss happy.

286
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:21,000
- Okay.
- Okay, be careful.

287
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:26,267
You all know

288
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,867
how hard our family has been
going through

289
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:31,167
because of the loss
of our father,

290
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:34,733
Mayor Joaquin "El Hepe"
Guerrero.

291
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:37,600
El Hepe...

292
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:41,133
Like my father,

293
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:45,133
will continue his fight
against crime.

294
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:47,833
As your new mayor,

295
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:50,500
I promise you all...

296
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:53,533
that I will continue
his projects.

297
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,100
A peaceful Calabari

298
00:14:56,233 --> 00:15:01,400
where every home is not afraid
to sleep at night.

299
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:04,400
A peaceful Calabari...

300
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:06,433
where each of you
is not afraid to walk

301
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:11,000
on the street at any time.

302
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:13,967
But I can't do this alone.

303
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:17,533
I need your help and unity,

304
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:19,033
like a family...

305
00:15:19,167 --> 00:15:20,733
One home.

306
00:15:20,867 --> 00:15:22,600
Let's work together,

307
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:27,600
and Calabari will achieve
true peace.

308
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:29,600
Thank you all very much.

309
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,967
Thank you.

310
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,367
What did you see
in your visions, Alma?

311
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,400
I saw a rainbow.

312
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:45,600
And...

313
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:50,433
I also saw a street sign,
but not a complete one.

314
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:53,767
What's written
on that street sign?

315
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:56,600
Raf...

316
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:58,300
Sa...

317
00:15:58,433 --> 00:16:00,033
Saraf...

318
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,433
Saraf!

319
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:03,533
That's what I saw!

320
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,433
Sorry, I'm really sorry.

321
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,400
No, it's okay, Alma.

322
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,367
You don't need to apologize.

323
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:14,600
Are you sure
that's a street sign you saw?

324
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:16,533
I haven't read anything yet.

325
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:18,800
Saraf is the name of the street.

326
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:20,200
I'm sorry.

327
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,233
That's all I saw.

328
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:24,967
Where did you see that rainbow
you're talking about?

329
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,133
Why did you see it

330
00:16:26,267 --> 00:16:29,267
in the sky,
or was it house paint?

331
00:16:30,233 --> 00:16:33,067
It's not clear to me where.

332
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:39,567
Okay.

333
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:43,367
That's probably enough
for now.

334
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:45,700
Thank you very much
for your help.

335
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:51,367
Noble, look at this victim.

336
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,500
He's hurting his child.

337
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:55,200
Really, Ma'am?

338
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:57,500
And this one...

339
00:16:57,633 --> 00:16:59,600
he cheats on her lovers.

340
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:01,500
Cheater.

341
00:17:01,633 --> 00:17:04,933
Then this one is a scammer.

342
00:17:05,067 --> 00:17:08,700
Oh, Noble, let's review
the case files we have.

343
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:11,500
Let's see if the victims
did anything wrong.

344
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:15,833
I don't think this is just
a random killing.

345
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,433
Maybe this isn't
just a hate crime.

346
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:26,333
Congratulations, Mayor!

347
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:27,500
We support you.

348
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,033
- Thank you, thank you.
- You're our idol, El Hepe Jr.

349
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,967
Let's just work together,
but thank you.

350
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:34,700
You can count on us, Mayor.

351
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,400
Oh, just enjoy yourself,
there's food in the back.

352
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:38,200
- Thank you, Mayor!
- Okay, okay.

353
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:40,933
Did you see Mommy?

354
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,567
She already went home already.

355
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,300
She went home?

356
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:46,567
She didn't tell me.

357
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,067
- Glen!
- Faye.

358
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,233
Congratulations again.

359
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,267
Of course,
I will help you fulfill

360
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,233
Dad's vision for Calabari.

361
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:55,800
Thanks.

362
00:17:55,933 --> 00:17:57,333
I'm expecting that, Faye.

363
00:17:59,967 --> 00:18:00,967
Mayor, congratulations.

364
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,367
Oh...

365
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:04,867
Vince, you're here.

366
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,933
Are you with
your partner, Allan?

367
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,167
No, Mayor.

368
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,367
He's busy right now.

369
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,600
Oh, is that so?

370
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:16,467
He's the one I told you
as my plus one.

371
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:17,633
What?

372
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:22,567
Wow.

373
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,833
Well, I didn't expect that.

374
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,433
Okay, Faye, I have some people
to talk to.

375
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:33,733
I have, I have to go to them.

376
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:35,200
There's food there.

377
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,733
You take care of him first.

378
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:38,467
Okay, okay, Glen.

379
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,267
- Let's go?
- Okay.

380
00:18:46,467 --> 00:18:47,333
Noble, look at this.

381
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:48,433
Ma'am.

382
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:51,800
All gay victims

383
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:53,533
are either cheater,

384
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:56,100
abusive parents, or scammers.

385
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,300
That seems to be the pattern
of the killer,

386
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:02,033
not just gay.

387
00:19:02,167 --> 00:19:04,733
Could it be just a coincidence?

388
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,633
It's possible...

389
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,600
but this is just my theory,

390
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:14,433
so don't tell anyone, okay?

391
00:19:14,567 --> 00:19:17,133
Maybe I'll get a bad shot again
from Chief later.

392
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:18,567
Copy, Ma'am.

393
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:30,733
Bok.

394
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,233
That's a bit vague.

395
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:34,233
I've never heard
of a Saraf street.

396
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:35,600
Who knows, Bok.

397
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:38,067
Her hints are different.

398
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,200
Hints?

399
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,233
Alma's visions,

400
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:43,233
they're like a puzzle,
you have to put it together

401
00:19:43,367 --> 00:19:44,967
but the pieces are missing.

402
00:19:47,133 --> 00:19:49,267
I know what we're doing
may sound impossible, Bok...

403
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,667
But I've proven that Alma's
visions have come true.

404
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:57,567
So if we really want to save
this killer's next victim,

405
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:01,333
we have no choice
but to solve this puzzle.

406
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,200
My god, Captain.

407
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,667
Those gays,

408
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:17,967
they actually fought in front
of the dead, right?

409
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:22,633
But you know, when they realized
they both lost...

410
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:25,167
They're both pitiful, Captain.

411
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,400
Hi, Grandmother.

412
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:31,400
- Oh, my grandchild. Hi.
- Bobby.

413
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:33,667
- Abdul, oh, Grandmother.
- Hey.

414
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,767
Hey.

415
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:39,067
- Oh, what?
- Hey, how was the office?

416
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:44,400
Oh, well, I got scolded,
big time.

417
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:48,733
- What?
- I'm doing a desk job for now.

418
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,333
But it's okay.

419
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:52,333
Whatever they ask me to do,

420
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:53,933
I'll do it properly.

421
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:59,067
So how's the investigation
going, Bobby?

422
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:01,933
The one about Tootsie's killer?

423
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,967
Well, there's no clear
suspect yet.

424
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:08,300
Oh my...

425
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:11,167
I hope that killer gets caught.

426
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:15,800
Even if Zondra and Tootsie
did something bad,

427
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:18,300
They probably didn't deserve
what happened to them.

428
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:22,000
Wait. Did something bad?

429
00:21:22,133 --> 00:21:23,533
What do you mean?

430
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,767
Oh, Bobby,

431
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:30,267
we found out that Tootsie
is a cheater.

432
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,867
She cheated on her spouse,

433
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:34,433
and she cheated on her lover
at the same time.

434
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:36,433
And Zondra,

435
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,900
she's hurting
her daughter Marie.

436
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:40,700
She has a big bruise on her arm.

437
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:46,667
Bobby, are you okay?

438
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,433
Grandmother, we found some cold
cases earlier.

439
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:53,867
Then the way he killed
the victim was the same.

440
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,133
The weapon he used
was an ice pick.

441
00:21:55,267 --> 00:21:56,600
Oh, so you mean, Bobby,

442
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:59,633
it's possible that the killer
in your cold cases is...

443
00:21:59,767 --> 00:22:02,333
Also the one who killed
Zondra and Tootsie?

444
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,300
This is the connection
I'm looking for.

445
00:22:25,433 --> 00:22:26,800
He also visited Monty!

446
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:28,933
Yes, that's why Chief
needs to know!

447
00:22:29,067 --> 00:22:30,633
Don't we have
a lot of gay friends?

448
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:32,300
It seems like we need
to check on them.

449
00:22:32,433 --> 00:22:33,200
Do you miss them?

450
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,667
I just wanted to warn them

451
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,333
about this serial killer.

452
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:38,467
He stabbed him with an ice pick
several times.

453
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,967
When I told the police
who the suspect was,

454
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,567
they didn't believe me.

455
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,767
Do you have a suspect?

456
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:46,233
Just the name
of the street, Saraf?

457
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:47,333
And then the color
of the rainbow?

458
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:48,567
Where are you going to find it,

459
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:49,867
and what does it mean?

460
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,433
I think I know how to solve
that puzzle.

461
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:53,867
This is my son.

462
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,167
This is Mateo Ramos.
